📘 Monolith DB vs Microservices DB (15 min)
1️⃣ Monolith Database
Definition

Single application → One shared database

[Monolith App]
     │
     ▼
   ONE DATABASE


All modules share same DB:

User

Account

Transaction

Payments

Notifications

Advantages ✅

Simple to build

Easy joins across tables

Strong ACID transactions

Easy debugging

No network calls

Disadvantages ❌

Hard to scale

Single DB = bottleneck

One failure affects all

Hard to migrate to microservices

Tight coupling between modules

2️⃣ Microservices Database
Definition

Each service has its own database

User Service → User DB
Account Service → Account DB
Transaction Service → Transaction DB
Notification Service → Notification DB


Services communicate via:

REST API

Kafka / Events

gRPC

Advantages ✅

Independent scaling

Fault isolation

Loose coupling

Technology flexibility

Easier deployments

Disadvantages ❌

No cross-service joins

Distributed transactions complex

Data duplication sometimes

Network latency

Hard debugging

3️⃣ Key Difference (Important)
Feature	Monolith	Microservices
Database	One shared	Per service
Transaction	Easy (ACID)	Hard (Distributed)
Scaling	Limited	Independent
Failure	Whole app	One service
Deployment	Single	Multiple
Complexity	Low	High
